    <summary>Opentrack is a head tracking software for Windows, Linux, and macOS</summary>
    <projectSourceUrl>https://github.com/opentrack/opentrack</projectSourceUrl>
    <description>Opentrack is an application dedicated to tracking user's head movements and relaying the information to games and flight simulation software.

    You can use multiple tracking sources :
    - PointTracker by Patrick Ruoff, freetrack-like light sources
    - Oculus Rift DK1, DK2, CV, and legacy/knockoff versions
    - Paper marker support via the ArUco library
    - Razer Hydra
    - Relaying via UDP from a different computer
    - Relaying UDP via FreePIE-specific Android app
    - Joystick analog axes
    - Windows Phone tracker over opentrack UDP protocol
    - Arduino with custom firmware
    - Intel RealSense 3D cameras
    - BBC micro:bit, LEGO, sensortag support via S2Bot

    And it is compatible with multiple output system like TrackIR :
    - SimConnect for newer Microsoft Flight Simulator
    - freetrack implementation
    - Relaying UDP to another computer
    - Virtual joystick output
    - Wine freetrack glue protocol
    - X-Plane plugin
    - Tablet-like mouse output
    - FlightGear
    - FSUIPC for Microsoft Flight Simulator 2002/2004
    - SteamVR through a bridge 
    
    ![screenshot](https://cdn.rawgit.com/Akipe/chocolatey-packages/e71705ae/icons/opentrack/opentrack-screenshot.png)
    </description>
